				<div style="font-style:italic">Pot probably would be as cheap as Cigarettes once it could be grown on the scale of Tobacco.  As to whether we'd want that, well you just admitted that DARE lies and pot isn't a gateway drug.  Thus, whether we wanted it would depends on the harm from pot, for which there is little evidence.</div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>There is, of course, harm from smoking pot. If nothing else, you're still smoking, and it is likely very similar to cigarette harms in that particular. <br />
<br />
What we should be concerned with, however, is whether there is additional harm beyond that created by the method of administration, which you rightly note is scanty.</div>
		<!-- / message -->

		

		

		

		

		

	</td>
